        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- hardens plugin-owned schema and metadata boundaries found during fuzzing with synthetic `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` fixtures\n- latest refresh hardens `tools.catalog`: active registry tool metadata and deferred plugin tool rows are now projected through bounded field and array-element reads before catalog output is built\n- keeps the draft PR branch updated as work continues; current head is `f0ec6fe7bb7c272ba08f9b00da1c622f7439d0cf`, proven on `origin/main` at `f848a6f7f74be72bc9e1868770c300c2f100eb87`\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/gateway/server-methods/tools-catalog.ts src/gateway/server-methods/tools-catalog.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD -- src/gateway/server-methods/tools-catalog.ts src/gateway/server-methods/tools-catalog.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/tools-catalog.ts src/gateway/server-methods/tools-catalog.test.ts`\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/gateway/server-methods/tools-catalog.test.ts --reporter=verbose`: 1 file passed, 8 tests passed\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`: clean on the `tools.catalog` metadata slice\n- scrubbed diff/spec/PR body for the reported plugin name and private local paths\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin-owned schema, metadata, command metadata, hook registration, tool registration options, CLI registration options, bundled agent tool result middleware options, captured middleware options, captured capability id surfaces, memory embedding provider registration, runtime embedding adapter merge/direct lookup, process-global embedding provider registry restore/list/register paths, migration provider runtime resolution, provider contract registry resolution, setup-only provider/backend runtime registration, compaction provider registration, capability provider runtime resolution, provider runtime hook lookup, shared provider resolver projection, active runtime CLI backend projection, provider discovery entry projection, explicit web provider public artifact projection, document/web-content extractor public artifact projection, trusted tool policy decision handling, Gateway Control UI descriptor projection, Gateway plugin session action dispatch, dynamic plugin session action method-scope resolution, plugin-registered Gateway method descriptor scope resolution, channel plugin Gateway method discovery, and `tools.catalog` active registry metadata projection no longer trust crashy getters, revoked proxies, mutable arrays/records, malformed runtime entries, malformed ids, unreadable aliases, unreadable hook aliases, unreadable labels/auth fields, unreadable backend configs, unreadable CLI commands, hostile callback metadata, throwing provider/extractor factories, unreadable public artifact metadata, throwing trusted policy evaluators, unreadable trusted policy decision fields, unreadable gateway descriptor metadata, unreadable session action metadata, malformed matched action scopes, unreadable gateway method descriptor names/scopes, unreadable channel gateway method arrays/elements, unreadable tool metadata entries, unreadable tool metadata records, unreadable deferred tool entries, or unreadable deferred tool ownership fields while healthy sibling registrations continue where the surface is availability-oriented and security-sensitive policy/scope failures fail closed.\n\nReal environment tested: local linked OpenClaw worktree on the draft PR branch, rebased onto `origin/main` at `f848a6f7f74be72bc9e1868770c300c2f100eb87`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: ran focused formatting, diff check, linting, Vitest, and autoreview commands listed in Verification after the `tools.catalog` metadata slice; after the final rebase, reran formatting, diff check, linting, and Vitest on the rebased head.\n\nEvidence after fix: `tools.catalog` tests now cover unreadable active registry tool metadata array entries, unreadable metadata records, unreadable deferred tool array entries, unreadable deferred tool plugin ids, and preservation of a healthy `mockplugin_deferred` tool with its plugin-owned display label, description, risk, tags, and optional flag.\n\nObserved result after fix: malformed active registry tool metadata no longer crashes `tools.catalog`; unreadable malformed plugin-owned entries are skipped, healthy deferred plugin tools still appear, and catalog metadata remains scoped to the owning plugin id plus tool name.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad Blacksmith/Testbox changed gate and AWS Crabbox broad gate were not rerun for this refresh; current proof is the targeted Gateway tool-catalog fuzz surface plus formatter/lint/autoreview checks.\n",
